51.1	Nobel_Prize_in_Literature	Nobel Prize in Literature	Since 1901, the Nobel Prize in Literature . Though individual works are sometimes cited as being particularly noteworthy, here "Work" refers to an author's work as a whole. The Swedish Academy decides who, if anyone, will receive the prize in any given year. The academy announces the name of the chosen laureate in early October. It is one of the five Nobel Prizes established by the will of Alfred Nobel in 1895; the others are the Nobel Prize in Chemistry, Nobel Prize in Physics, Nobel Peace Prize, and Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Nobel2008Literature_news_conference1.jpg/220px-Nobel2008Literature_news_conference1.jpg
